title: Roundup (Oct. 22): Hereford field hockey beats Dulaney for Baltimore County title
text:
Roundup (Oct. 22): Hereford field hockey beats Dulaney for Baltimore County title Hereford field hockey Brian Krista / Baltimore Sun Media Group 
Hereford teammates swarm around their goalie after defeating Dulaney, 1-0, during the Baltimore County field hockey championship at Lansdowne High School on Thursday, Oct 22, 2015. 
Hereford teammates swarm around their goalie after defeating Dulaney, 1-0, during the Baltimore County field hockey championship at Lansdowne High School on Thursday, Oct 22, 2015. (Brian Krista / Baltimore Sun Media Group) From Sun staff reports 
Rachel Karwacki scored the game-winner on a breakaway in the first half as the No. 8 Hereford field hockey team upset No. 5 Dulaney, 1-0, in the Baltimore County championship game Thursday at Lansdowne. 
The Bulls improved to 12-2-1, and the Lions fell to 11-2 as their 11-game winning streak ended. 
No. 1 Archbishop Spalding 6, Fallston 0: Erin Shanahan scored twice as the Cavaliers finished their regular season with a 15-0-1 record. The visiting Cougars fell to 7-6. 
Boys soccer 
No. 2 Mount Hebron 3, Long Reach 0: Mike Linsenmeyer scored twice, and the Vikings (12-2) beat the host Lightning (6-7) for their first Howard County title since 2006.
